      "SOPHOCLES (~496-406 BCE): introduced the third actor; reduced the chorus's role; increased dramatic complexity. Famous for psychological depth of characters, the theme of hamartia (tragic flaw leading to downfall). Oedipus Rex considered the perfect tragedy by Aristotle in the Poetics. Key plays: Oedipus Rex, Oedipus at Colonus, Antigone (the Theban plays), Ajax, Electra, Philoctetes, Women of Trachis (Heracles's death)",
